<h2 id="guidelines">Guidelines</h2>
<h3 id="title">What about &lt;menu&gt;?</h3>
<p>This element is only loosely based on the <code>HTMLMenuElement</code> interface because that spec is incomplete and looks to be deprecated.</p>
<h3 id="accessibility">Accessibility</h3>
<p>There are no accessibility recommendations for menu at this time. This post <a
        href="https://adrianroselli.com/2017/10/dont-use-aria-menu-roles-for-site-nav.html">https://adrianroselli.com/2017/10/dont-use-aria-menu-roles-for-site-nav.html</a> seems reasonable and accurate enough to say that simple markup like anchor tags in menus is sufficient.</p>
